# Section 6 — Google ADK Internals

---

# 6.1 Introduction

Google Agent Development Kit (Google ADK) is the orchestration framework used to build AI agents.

Unlike traditional chatbot frameworks that simply send prompts to a language model, ADK introduces an execution framework capable of:

- Maintaining sessions
- Managing conversations
- Registering tools
- Invoking MCP servers
- Coordinating multiple external systems
- Returning structured responses

Google ADK therefore acts as the operating system for the AI agent.

Gemini is only one component inside ADK.

---

# 6.2 ADK Architecture

The architecture inside ADK can be represented as:

```
                User Question
                       │
                       ▼
                 Google ADK
                       │
         ┌─────────────┼─────────────┐
         │             │             │
         ▼             ▼             ▼

     Session       LlmAgent      Runner

         │             │             │
         └─────────────┼─────────────┘
                       │
                       ▼
                Gemini 2.5 Flash
                       │
                Tool Planning
                       │
                Tool Invocation
                       │
                MCP Servers
                       │
                Tool Results
                       │
                 Final Response
```

Google ADK coordinates the entire workflow.

